{"title_page": "Danel Sinani", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Danel Sinani\n| image = \n| imagesize = \n| caption = \n| fullname = Danel Sinani\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1997|4|5|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Belgrade]], [[Serbia and Montenegro|Yugoslavia]]\n| height = 1.85 m\n| position = [[Winger (association football)|Winger]]\n| currentclub = [[F91 Dudelange|Dudelange]] <!-- Not Norwich player until next season -->\n| clubnumber = 9\n| youthyears1 = {{0|0000}}\u20132012\n| youthclubs1 = [[FC Differdange 03]]\n| youthyears2 = 2012\u20132014\n| youthclubs2 = [[Racing FC Union Luxembourg|Racing FC]]\n| years1 = 2014\u20132017\n| clubs1 = [[Racing FC Union Luxembourg|Racing FC]]\n| caps1 = 72\n| goals1 = 15\n| years2 = 2017\u2013\n| clubs2 = [[F91 Dudelange|Dudelange]]\n| caps2 = 61\n| goals2 = 30\n| nationalyears1 = 2015\n| nationalteam1 = [[Luxembourg national under-19 football team|Luxembourg U19]]\n| nationalcaps1 = 3\n| nationalgoals1 = 0\n| nationalyears2 = 2015\u2013\n| nationalteam2 = [[Luxembourg national under-21 football team|Luxembourg U21]]\n| nationalcaps2 = 11\n| nationalgoals2 = 1\n| nationalyears3 = 2017\u2013\n| nationalteam3 = [[Luxembourg national football team|Luxembourg]]\n| nationalcaps3 = 21\n| nationalgoals3 = 3\n| club-update = 15:08, 26 February 2020 (UTC)\n| nationalteam-update = 17 November 2019\n| medaltemplates = \n}}\n'''Danel Sinani''' (born 5 April 1997) is a [[Luxembourgers|Luxembourgish]] professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays club football for [[F91 Dudelange]], as a [[midfielder (association football)|midfielder]]. He has signed for [[Norwich City F.C.|Norwich City]] for the 2020\u201321 season.\n\n==Club career==\nSinani has played club football for [[Racing FC Union Luxembourg]] and [[F91 Dudelange]].<ref name = \"NFT\">{{NFT player|pid=68789}}</ref><ref>{{soccerway|danel-sinani/411065}}</ref> He was one two [[Luxembourg National Division]] with Dudelange.<ref name=Canaries/> In November 2018, he scored against [[Olympiacos F.C.]] the first ever goal for a Luxembourgish club in the group stage of a major European competition.<ref name=Canaries>{{cite web| url= https://www.canaries.co.uk/News/2020/april/factfile-danel-sinani/| title= Factfile: Danel Sinani| publisher=[[Norwich City F.C.]]| date=10 April 2020| accessdate=11 April 2020}}</ref> In 2019, he scored two goals in a [[Europa League]] match against [[Sevilla FC|Sevilla]].<ref>{{cite news| url= https://www.tageblatt.lu/headlines/europa-league-sinani-rettet-die-f91-ehre-gegen-sevilla/| title= Europa League: Sinani rettet die F91-Ehre gegen Sevilla| language=de| work=[[Tageblatt]]| date=7 November 2019| accessdate=11 April 2020}}</ref> As of 2020, he has scored 13 goals in [[UEFA Champions League]] and Europa League matches.<ref name=Canaries/>\n\nIn April 2020, he signed for [[Norwich City F.C.|Norwich City]] for the 2020\u201321 season.<ref name=BBC>{{cite news| url= https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/52249423| title= Norwich sign Luxembourg forward Danel Sinani| work=[[BBC Sport]]| date=10 April 2020| accessdate=10 April 2020}}</ref> His start date is dependent on the resumption of the [[2019\u201320 Premier League]] due to the [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in the United Kingdom|coronavirus pandemic]].<ref name=PinkUn>{{cite news| url= https://www.pinkun.com/norwich-city/city-complete-sinani-deal-1-6603448| title= Norwich City complete signing of Danel Sinani| work=[[The Pink'un]]| date=10 April 2020| accessdate=10 April 2020}}</ref> He is expected to be the first Luxembourgish Norwich City player.<ref name=PinkUn/>\n\n==International career==\nHe made his international debut for [[Luxembourg national football team|Luxembourg]] in 2017.<ref name=\"NFT\"/> [[Kosovo national football team|Kosovo]] approached Sinani about representing them internationally, as his parents are from [[Draga\u0161]]. Sinani refused the meeting to discuss it, as he sees Luxembourg as his home.<ref name=SK>{{cite news| url= https://www.sportske.net/vest/medjunarodni-fudbal/srbiju-veceras-napada-beogradjanin-danel-sinani-386875.html| title= Srbiju ve\u010deras napada Beogra\u0111anin Danel Sinani!| language=bo| last=CVETKOVI\u0106| first=Ivan| work=sportske.net| date=10 September 2019| accessdate=11 April 2020}}</ref> Sinani scored three goals for Luxembourg during their [[2018\u201319 UEFA Nations League D]] campaign.<ref name=Canaries/>\n\n==Awards==\nIn 2019, Sinani was given the Luxembourg Footballer of the Year award. It was his first award of the trophy, known as the Wanderpokal Challenge Guy Greffrath (Challenge Guy Greffrath challenge cup).<ref name=Wort>{{cite news| url= https://www.wort.lu/de/sport/danel-sinani-ist-fussballer-des-jahres-5d8e6570da2cc1784e34c5b7| title= Danel Sinani ist Fu\u00dfballer des Jahres| work=wort.lu| date=27 September 2019| accessdate=11 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nSinani was born in [[Belgrade]], [[Serbia]], [[FR Yugoslavia]] to ethnic [[Gorani people|Gorani]] parents from [[Draga\u0161]]. He moved to Luxembourg along with his family at the age of 5.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://sportekspres.com/historia-e-danel-sinanit-djalit-nga-sharri-qe-nuk-eshte-shqiptar/|title=Historia e Danel Sinanit, djalit nga Sharri q\u00eb nuk \u00ebsht\u00eb\u2026 shqiptar|trans-title=The history of Danel Sinani, the boy from Sharr who is not an\u2026 Albanian|publisher=Sport Ekspres|language=Albanian|date=5 September 2018|accessdate=3 January 2019}}</ref>\n\n==International goals==\n:''Scores and results list Luxembourg's goal tally first.''<ref name=\"NFT\"/>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! No !! Date !! Venue !! Opponent !! Score !! Result !! Competition\n|-\n| 1 || 8 September 2018 || [[Stade Josy Barthel]], [[Luxembourg City]], Luxembourg || {{fb|MDA}} || align=center | '''3'''\u20130 || align=center | 4\u20130 || rowspan=3| [[2018\u201319 UEFA Nations League D]]\n|-\n| 2 || 11 September 2018 || [[San Marino Stadium]], [[Serravalle (San Marino)|Serravalle]], San Marino || {{fb|San Marino}} || align=center | '''3'''\u20130 || align=center | 3\u20130\n|-\n| 3 || 15 October 2018 || Stade Josy Barthel, Luxembourg City, Luxembourg || {{fb|San Marino}} || align=center | '''2'''\u20130 || align=center | 3\u20130\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Luxembourgian Footballer of the Year}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Sinani, Danel}}\n[[Category:1997 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Gorani people]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Belgrade]]\n[[Category:Luxembourgian footballers]]\n[[Category:Luxembourg international footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football midfielders]]\n[[Category:Racing FC Union Luxembourg players]]\n[[Category:F91 Dudelange players]]\n\n\n{{Luxembourg-footy-bio-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Danel Sinani\n| image = \n| imagesize = \n| caption = \n| fullname = Danel Sinani\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1997|4|5|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Belgrade]], [[Serbia and Montenegro|Yugoslavia]]\n| height = 1.85 m\n| position = [[Winger (association football)|Winger]]\n| currentclub = [[F91 Dudelange|Dudelange]] <!-- Not Norwich player until next season -->\n| clubnumber = 9\n| youthyears1 = {{0|0000}}\u20132012\n| youthclubs1 = [[FC Differdange 03]]\n| youthyears2 = 2012\u20132014\n| youthclubs2 = [[Racing FC Union Luxembourg|Racing FC]]\n| years1 = 2014\u20132017\n| clubs1 = [[Racing FC Union Luxembourg|Racing FC]]\n| caps1 = 72\n| goals1 = 15\n| years2 = 2017\u2013\n| clubs2 = [[F91 Dudelange|Dudelange]]\n| caps2 = 61\n| goals2 = 30\n| nationalyears1 = 2015\n| nationalteam1 = [[Luxembourg national under-19 football team|Luxembourg U19]]\n| nationalcaps1 = 3\n| nationalgoals1 = 0\n| nationalyears2 = 2015\u2013\n| nationalteam2 = [[Luxembourg national under-21 football team|Luxembourg U21]]\n| nationalcaps2 = 11\n| nationalgoals2 = 1\n| nationalyears3 = 2017\u2013\n| nationalteam3 = [[Luxembourg national football team|Luxembourg]]\n| nationalcaps3 = 21\n| nationalgoals3 = 3\n| club-update = 15:08, 26 February 2020 (UTC)\n| nationalteam-update = 17 November 2019\n| medaltemplates = \n}}\n'''Danel Sinani''' (born 5 April 1997) is a [[Luxembourgers|Luxembourgish]] professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays club football for [[F91 Dudelange]], as a [[midfielder (association football)|midfielder]]. He has signed for [[Norwich City F.C.|Norwich City]] for the 2020\u201321 season.\n\n==Club career==\nSinani has played club football for [[Racing FC Union Luxembourg]] and [[F91 Dudelange]].<ref name = \"NFT\">{{NFT player|pid=68789}}</ref><ref>{{soccerway|danel-sinani/411065}}</ref> He was one two [[Luxembourg National Division]] with Dudelange.<ref name=Canaries/> In November 2018, he scored against [[Olympiacos F.C.]] the first ever goal for a Luxembourgish club in the group stage of a major European competition.<ref name=Canaries>{{cite web| url= https://www.canaries.co.uk/News/2020/april/factfile-danel-sinani/| title= Factfile: Danel Sinani| publisher=[[Norwich City F.C.]]| date=10 April 2020| accessdate=11 April 2020}}</ref> In 2019, he scored two goals in a [[Europa League]] match against [[Sevilla FC|Sevilla]].<ref>{{cite news| url= https://www.tageblatt.lu/headlines/europa-league-sinani-rettet-die-f91-ehre-gegen-sevilla/| title= Europa League: Sinani rettet die F91-Ehre gegen Sevilla| language=de| work=[[Tageblatt]]| date=7 November 2019| accessdate=11 April 2020}}</ref> As of 2020, he has scored 13 goals in [[Champions League]] and Europa League matches.<ref name=Canaries/>\n\nIn April 2020, he signed for [[Norwich City F.C.|Norwich City]] for the 2020\u201321 season.<ref name=BBC>{{cite news| url= https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/52249423| title= Norwich sign Luxembourg forward Danel Sinani| work=[[BBC Sport]]| date=10 April 2020| accessdate=10 April 2020}}</ref> His start date is dependent on the resumption of the [[2019\u201320 Premier League]] due to the [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in the United Kingdom|coronavirus pandemic]].<ref name=PinkUn>{{cite news| url= https://www.pinkun.com/norwich-city/city-complete-sinani-deal-1-6603448| title= Norwich City complete signing of Danel Sinani| work=[[The Pink'un]]| date=10 April 2020| accessdate=10 April 2020}}</ref> He is expected to be the first Luxembourgish Norwich City player.<ref name=PinkUn/>\n\n==International career==\nHe made his international debut for [[Luxembourg national football team|Luxembourg]] in 2017.<ref name=\"NFT\"/> [[Kosovo national football team|Kosovo]] approached Sinani about representing them internationally, as his parents are from [[Draga\u0161]]. Sinani refused the meeting to discuss it, as he sees Luxembourg as his home.<ref name=SK>{{cite news| url= https://www.sportske.net/vest/medjunarodni-fudbal/srbiju-veceras-napada-beogradjanin-danel-sinani-386875.html| title= Srbiju ve\u010deras napada Beogra\u0111anin Danel Sinani!| language=bo| last=CVETKOVI\u0106| first=Ivan| work=sportske.net| date=10 September 2019| accessdate=11 April 2020}}</ref> Sinani scored three goals for Luxembourg during their [[2018\u201319 UEFA Nations League D]] campaign.<ref name=Canaries/>\n\n==Awards==\nIn 2019, Sinani was given the Luxembourg Footballer of the Year award. It was his first award of the trophy, known as the Wanderpokal Challenge Guy Greffrath (Challenge Guy Greffrath challenge cup).<ref name=Wort>{{cite news| url= https://www.wort.lu/de/sport/danel-sinani-ist-fussballer-des-jahres-5d8e6570da2cc1784e34c5b7| title= Danel Sinani ist Fu\u00dfballer des Jahres| work=wort.lu| date=27 September 2019| accessdate=11 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nSinani was born in [[Belgrade]], [[Serbia]], [[FR Yugoslavia]] to ethnic [[Gorani people|Gorani]] parents from [[Draga\u0161]]. He moved to Luxembourg along with his family at the age of 5.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://sportekspres.com/historia-e-danel-sinanit-djalit-nga-sharri-qe-nuk-eshte-shqiptar/|title=Historia e Danel Sinanit, djalit nga Sharri q\u00eb nuk \u00ebsht\u00eb\u2026 shqiptar|trans-title=The history of Danel Sinani, the boy from Sharr who is not an\u2026 Albanian|publisher=Sport Ekspres|language=Albanian|date=5 September 2018|accessdate=3 January 2019}}</ref>\n\n==International goals==\n:''Scores and results list Luxembourg's goal tally first.''<ref name=\"NFT\"/>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! No !! Date !! Venue !! Opponent !! Score !! Result !! Competition\n|-\n| 1 || 8 September 2018 || [[Stade Josy Barthel]], [[Luxembourg City]], Luxembourg || {{fb|MDA}} || align=center | '''3'''\u20130 || align=center | 4\u20130 || rowspan=3| [[2018\u201319 UEFA Nations League D]]\n|-\n| 2 || 11 September 2018 || [[San Marino Stadium]], [[Serravalle (San Marino)|Serravalle]], San Marino || {{fb|San Marino}} || align=center | '''3'''\u20130 || align=center | 3\u20130\n|-\n| 3 || 15 October 2018 || Stade Josy Barthel, Luxembourg City, Luxembourg || {{fb|San Marino}} || align=center | '''2'''\u20130 || align=center | 3\u20130\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Luxembourgian Footballer of the Year}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Sinani, Danel}}\n[[Category:1997 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Gorani people]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Belgrade]]\n[[Category:Luxembourgian footballers]]\n[[Category:Luxembourg international footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football midfielders]]\n[[Category:Racing FC Union Luxembourg players]]\n[[Category:F91 Dudelange players]]\n\n\n{{Luxembourg-footy-bio-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Joseph2302", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eClub career:dab fix", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Danel_Sinani"}
